The command somehow seems to be trying to build cloud and mobile targets.
using no_big_endian tags will not help with the command you are running, because you are not filtering with the "no_big_endian" tag in your command.
One immediate solution can be to exclude some more modules in your command. Could you try adding these at the end of your command:

-//tensorflow/core/platform/aws/... -//tensorflow/core-platform/cloud/... -//tensorflow/contrib/lite/... -//tensorflow/contrib/cloud/...

body:
The command somehow seems to be trying to build cloud and mobile targets.
using no_big_endian tags will not help with the command you are running, because you are not filtering with the "no_big_endian" tag in your command.
One immediate solution can be to exclude some more modules in your command. Could you try adding these at the end of your command:
```
-//tensorflow/core/platform/aws/... -//tensorflow/core-platform/cloud/... -//tensorflow/contrib/lite/... -//tensorflow/contrib/cloud/...
```
